quran[11]{c,v,t,f}:
  92,19,"And who has (in mind) no favour from anyone to be paid back,"
  92,20,"Except to seek the Countenance of his Lord, the Most High."
  92,21,"He surely will be pleased (when he enters Paradise)."
  96,7,"Because he considers himself self-sufficient."
  96,8,"Surely, unto your Lord is the return."
  96,9,"Have you (O Muhammad صلى الله عليه وسلم) seen him (i.e. Abû Jahl) who prevents"
  97,4,"Therein descend the angels and the Rûh [Jibrîl (Gabrîl)] by Allâh’s Permission with all Decrees,"
  97,5,"(All that night), there is Peace (and Goodness from Allâh to His believing slaves) until the appearance of dawn.{1}",footnotes:1:(V.5) Narrated ‘Âishah رضي الله عنها: Allâh’s Messenger صلى الله عليه وسلم said, "Search for the Night of Qadr in the odd nights of the last ten nights of Ramadan." (Sahih Al-Bukhari, Vol. 3, Hadith No.234).
  98,1,"Those who disbelieve from among the people of the Scripture (Jews and Christians) and Al-Mushrikûn,{1} were not going to leave (their disbelief) until there came to them clear evidence.",footnotes:1:(V.1) Al-Mushrikûn: polytheists, pagans, idolaters and disbelievers in the Oneness of Allâh and His Messenger Muhammad صلى الله عليه وسلم.
  98,2,"A Messenger (Muhammad صلى الله عليه وسلم) from Allâh, reciting (the Qur’ân) purified pages [purified from Al-Bâtil (falsehood)]."
  98,3,"Wherein are correct and straight laws from Allâh."